\begin{MintedVerbatim}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}
name: generate\PYGZhy{}user\PYGZhy{}stories
\PYG{g+gu}{description: Generate user story files for every route in the app. Reads RouteConfig.tsx, groups related routes, creates structured user story markdown files in playwright/user\PYGZhy{}stories/. Skips files that already exist. Use when you want to generate user stories for e2e test planning.}
\PYG{g+gu}{\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}}

\PYG{g+gh}{\PYGZsh{} Generate User Stories from Routes}

This skill reads every route in the application and generates user story files that serve as input for a future e2e test\PYGZhy{}generation loop. Do NOT interview the user — autonomously explore the codebase and generate.

\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}

\PYG{g+gu}{\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{} 1 — Source of Truth}

\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYG{g+gs}{**Routes:**} \PYG{l+s+sb}{`apps/client/src/RouteConfig.tsx`} — the single source of truth for all routes.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYG{g+gs}{**E2E guidelines:**} \PYG{l+s+sb}{`apps/client/playwright/skill/SKILL.md`} — reference for auth fixtures and test conventions (used lightly, only in Preconditions).
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYG{g+gs}{**Route constants:**} \PYG{l+s+sb}{`apps/client/playwright/support/data/routes.ts`} — existing route constants for tests.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYG{g+gs}{**Output directory:**} \PYG{l+s+sb}{`apps/client/playwright/user\PYGZhy{}stories/`}

\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}

\PYG{g+gu}{\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{} 2 — Folder Structure}

Organise user story files by role:

\PYG{l+s+sb}{```markdown}
playwright/user\PYGZhy{}stories/
├── public/
│   ├── signin.md
│   ├── signup.md
│   └── ...
├── employee/
│   ├── me.md
│   ├── me\PYGZhy{}activities.md
│   └── ...
└── admin/
    ├── people.md
    ├── people\PYGZhy{}detail.md          ← parent
    ├── people\PYGZhy{}detail\PYGZhy{}jobs.md     ← child of people\PYGZhy{}detail
    ├── jobs.md
    ├── jobs\PYGZhy{}detail.md            ← parent
    ├── jobs\PYGZhy{}detail\PYGZhy{}people.md     ← child of jobs\PYGZhy{}detail
    └── ...
\PYG{l+s+sb}{```}

\PYG{g+gu}{\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{} Naming rules}

\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Role folders: \PYG{l+s+sb}{`public/`}, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`employee/`}, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`admin/`}
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }File names are derived from the route path with \PYG{l+s+sb}{`/`} replaced by \PYG{l+s+sb}{`\PYGZhy{}`}, stripping the role prefix.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Dynamic segments (\PYG{l+s+sb}{`:id`}, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`:personId`}) are replaced with \PYG{l+s+sb}{`detail`} for parent routes or dropped for child routes.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Examples:
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYG{l+s+sb}{`/signin`} → \PYG{l+s+sb}{`public/signin.md`}
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYG{l+s+sb}{`/employee/me`} → \PYG{l+s+sb}{`employee/me.md`}
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYG{l+s+sb}{`/employee/me/activities`} → \PYG{l+s+sb}{`employee/me\PYGZhy{}activities.md`}
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYG{l+s+sb}{`/hr/jobs/:id`} → \PYG{l+s+sb}{`admin/jobs\PYGZhy{}detail.md`}
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYG{l+s+sb}{`/hr/jobs/:id/people`} → \PYG{l+s+sb}{`admin/jobs\PYGZhy{}detail\PYGZhy{}people.md`}
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYG{l+s+sb}{`/hr/people/:id`} → \PYG{l+s+sb}{`admin/people\PYGZhy{}detail.md`}
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }\PYG{l+s+sb}{`/hr/settings/branding`} → \PYG{l+s+sb}{`admin/settings\PYGZhy{}branding.md`}

\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}

\PYG{g+gu}{\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{} 3 — Route Grouping Rules}

\PYG{g+gu}{\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{} 3.1 Parent/child pattern (default)}

When a route has sub\PYGZhy{}routes under a dynamic segment (e.g. \PYG{l+s+sb}{`/hr/jobs/:id/people`}, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`/hr/jobs/:id/history`}):

\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }The \PYG{g+gs}{**parent**} route (e.g. \PYG{l+s+sb}{`/hr/jobs/:id`}) gets its own file with shared context and preconditions.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Each \PYG{g+gs}{**child**} route gets its own file with a \PYG{l+s+sb}{`parent`} field in frontmatter pointing to the parent file.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Each child file has its own focused acceptance criteria, happy flow, and key interactions.

\PYG{g+gu}{\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{} 3.2 Wizard exception}

Sequential multi\PYGZhy{}step flows (e.g. \PYG{l+s+sb}{`/hr/development\PYGZhy{}plans/create/:personId/role\PYGZhy{}selection`}, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`step\PYGZhy{}2`}, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`step\PYGZhy{}3`}, \PYG{l+s+sb}{`step\PYGZhy{}4`}) are treated as a \PYG{g+gs}{**single file**}:

\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }All step routes listed in frontmatter.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }Acceptance criteria organised as sub\PYGZhy{}sections per step.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }One continuous happy flow covering the full sequence.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }File name: \PYG{l+s+sb}{`admin/development\PYGZhy{}plan\PYGZhy{}wizard.md`}

\PYG{g+gu}{\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{}\PYGZsh{} 3.3 Identifying wizards vs. tabs}

\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }If child routes are \PYG{g+gs}{**sequential steps**} of a single flow (user must go through them in order) → wizard pattern → single file.
\PYG{k}{\PYGZhy{}}\PYG{+w}{ }If child routes are \PYG{g+gs}{**independent views/tabs**} of a resource (user can visit any in any order) → parent/child pattern → separate files.

\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{}

so that [benefit].

